<title>JAPAN: Shin-Etsu Chemical to buy back 722,000 shares.</title>
<headline>Shin-Etsu Chemical to buy back 722,000 shares.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shin-Etsu Chemical Co Ltd, a producer of semiconductor silicon, said on Friday it would buy back 722,000 of its own shares to introduce a stock option scheme.</p>
<p>The maximum amount to be spent on the repurchase would be 2.5 billion yen, it said.  </p>
<p>The decision needs to be approved at its shareholders' meeting on June 27.</p>
<p>Stock options will be offered to a total 63 directors and executives. Directors will be offered 505,000 shares and executives 217,000 shares, Shin-Etsu said.</p>
